    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BLYTON, Wash, June 9.-Men\nare so scarce here that packing\ngirls are putting on overalls and\npicking cherries in the orchards.\nENTERPRISE, Ore, June o.\nForty carloads of sheep for Seattle\nhave been shipped from here. They\nare from the ranges of the biggest\nsheep men.\n\n\nWENATCHEE, Wash, June o.\nPreparations are being made for the\nremoval of the postoffice to the fine\nnew building. The salary of Post\nmaster Terry Ross has been raised\nfrom $4,000 to $4,000.\n\n\nRITZVILLE, Wash, June o.\nOliver Sanderson left yesterday for\nAlberta, Canada. He has fallen\nheir there to $4,000 in cash and\n200 acres of land. Sanderson did\nodd jobs here for a living.\n\n\nCOEUR D'ALENE, Idaho, June 8.\nOn June 16 democrats of Koote-\nmai county will hold a banquet here.\nPlates will be laid for $50.\n\n\nLEWISTON, Idaho, June 9.-Mrs.\nGertie Cannon, 16 year old bride,\nhas confessed to the theft of jew\nelry from Mrs. Lee Allen of Pull\nman."
    }
